text: I am confident that we can serve our men and women in uniform and our veterans as well as they have served this country. —The First Lady
If you’re a woman veteran, I want to ask you to stand tall and share your story. —The First Lady #WomenVets
If you’re a healthcare provider, make sure every veteran gets the care they’re entitled to. —The First Lady #WomenVets
If you’re a CEO, a hiring manager, raise the bar and commit to employing more women veterans. —The First Lady #WomenVets
If you’re a member of Congress, work with us to ensure that all of our veterans get the support they deserve. —The First Lady #WomenVets
Today, I want to challenge everyone – to take action on behalf of our women veterans. —The First Lady on supporting our #WomenVets.
We all have a role to play in supporting our #WomenVets. Every single one of us needs to step up and do our part. —The First Lady
We set up a Women Veterans Call Center – staffed entirely by women – to answer questions for women veterans. —The First Lady #WomenVets
Over the past seven years, we’ve trained 2,400 veteran healthcare providers in women’s health. —The First Lady honoring #WomenVets
Women have sacrificed so much — they should never have to hide their accomplishments. —The First Lady on telling the story of our #WomenVets
One striking reality is that many women veterans don’t even self-identify as veterans. —The First Lady honoring #WomenVets
Thanks to brilliant, fearless women...more than 200,000 women are serving our country in just about every role and rank. —FLOTUS #WomenVets
